    ingredients: ["4.5 oz Trifecta Chicken Breasts, diced", "2 large Trifecta Eggs, rough chop", "1/2 Medium Cauliflower head, processed", "2 Garlic Cloves, rough chop", "1/2 Tsp of Salt", "2 Stalks, green onion, sliced into rounds, green and white separated", "1 Tbsp. Tamari (GF Soy Sauce)", "1 Tbsp. Sesame Oil", "1 Tsp. Black Sesame Seeds", "1/2 Avocado, medium", "Salt and Pepper, to taste"],
    instructions: ["Prepare the Cauliflower rice by cutting the cauliflower into florets and processing in a food processor until a grainy texture is achieved. Pulse for best results. Be careful not to process for too long, or the cauliflower will turn into mush.", "Chop trifecta chicken breast into bite-size squares, maintaining an even cut to ensure even heating. Set aside. Rough chop trifecta eggs to add to the rice later on.", "In sauté pan, over medium-high heat, heat 1 tbsp. of sesame oil and add garlic cloves and the white bulb of green onions. Lightly season with salt. Sauté until the onion and garlic begin to gain color. Immediately add the cauliflower rice.", "Deglaze pan with tamari, and immediately add diced chicken and chopped eggs. Sauté until heated through.", "Divide into two plates. Top with black sesame seeds, sliced bulb of green onions, and 1/4 avocado for each plate."],
