    ingredients: ["16 oz chicken, diced", "4 cups broccoli", "1 Tbsp. avocado oil", "1 Tbsp. sesame oil", "½ cup chicken broth, sodium-free", "½ cup coconut aminos", "3 Tbsp. lime juice", "1 Tbsp. honey", "1 Tbsp. ginger, fresh, grated", "1 tsp. garlic powder", "½ tsp. red pepper flakes", "1 tsp. cornstarch", "2 tsp. water", "Salt and pepper", "Sesame seeds, for garnish"],
    instructions: ["Preheat oven to 400F. Dice chicken into even cubes and transfer the chicken to a medium bowl. Season lightly with salt and pepper and keep to the side. Clean your station by washing your knife and cutting board.", "If using raw chicken, roast your chicken in the oven for 12 minutes. Once ready, remove from the oven and cool down. If using Trifecta A La Carte Chicken, cube the chicken and transfer to a medium bowl until needed. Clean your station. Cut the broccoli into even florets. Season with salt, pepper, and avocado oil. Roast for 12 minutes in the oven. Feel free to do this while the chicken is cooking.", "If using Trifecta’s A La Carte Broccoli, remove all 16 ounces from the container and lightly season with salt and pepper. Hold on the side as there is no need to roast.", "In a small saucepan, combine sesame oil, avocado oil, chicken broth, coconut aminos, lime juice, fresh ginger, honey garlic powder, and red pepper flakes. Bring to a boil, mix often, and then reduce heat to medium to an active simmer.", "Prepare your cornstarch slurry. The slurry will thicken the sauce - we don’t want to reduce the sauce too much as the salt will get stronger as the liquid evaporates. Add 1 teaspoon at a time, mixing constantly. 2 teaspoons of the slurry should suffice but feel free to add extra for further sauce body.", "Once the sauce has thickened, pour on top of the cooked cubed chicken. Plate with 1 cup of roasted broccoli on each plate, and 4 ounces of chicken right on top. Sprinkle with any remaining additional sauce. Garnish with sesame seeds."],
